  "prompt": "Is there a database with all nutritional information?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several databases that provide comprehensive nutritional information for a wide range of foods. Some of the most popular and widely used databases include:\n\n1. **USDA National Nutrient Database**: The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) provides a comprehensive database that contains detailed nutritional information on thousands of food items. It is regularly updated and widely used by nutrition professionals.\n\n2. **FoodData Central**: This is an extension of the USDA database, offering not only nutrient values but also additional food characteristics such as food groups and sources.\n\n3. **NutritionData (Self.com)**: This online resource allows users to search for nutritional information on various foods and recipes.\n\n4. **MyFitnessPal**: An app and website that provides extensive nutritional information and allows users to track their food intake. The database is user-contributed, which means it may include a wide range of foods, including many restaurant items.\n\n5. **Nutritionix**: This database focuses on restaurant and packaged foods and provides detailed nutritional information. It\u2019s used by various apps and websites for nutritional analysis.\n\n6. **Open Food Facts**: A collaborative database of food products that includes nutritional information and is accessible to the public.\n\n7. **CIQUAL**: The French food composition table, which provides detailed nutritional information for a wide range of food items commonly consumed in France.\n\nThese databases can be useful for individuals looking to understand their nutritional intake or for professionals in the field of nutrition and health. Each has its strengths, and the choice may depend on specific needs, such as international foods, restaurant items, or brand-specific products.",
